WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.226 --> 00:00:10.290
I just don't think

2
00:00:10.314 --> 00:00:12.292
that we have time
to be doing interviews.

3
00:00:12.316 --> 00:00:14.686
when we have a manuscript
to deliver in less than a month.

4
00:00:14.710 --> 00:00:17.167
Yes. we have a deadline.
but marketing is important.

5
00:00:17.191 --> 00:00:19.821
and <i>Dean's Catch</i> has
over a million subscribers.

6
00:00:19.845 --> 00:00:20.953
A mil?

7
00:00:20.977 --> 00:00:22.215
That's hard to believe

8
00:00:22.239 --> 00:00:24.870
with a stupid name
like <i>Dean's Catch.</i>

9
00:00:24.894 --> 00:00:26.480
Well. it used to be
a boring show

10
00:00:26.504 --> 00:00:28.743
about fishing reports
and nautical maps.

11
00:00:28.767 --> 00:00:31.224
until we started
solving mysteries and murders.

12
00:00:31.248 --> 00:00:33.555
so. he pivoted. and cashed in.

13
00:00:35.122 --> 00:00:36.229
You really don't like
this guy. do you?

14
00:00:36.253 --> 00:00:37.404
I've known him for years.

15
00:00:37.428 --> 00:00:39.015
He thinks
he's a real ladies' man.

16
00:00:39.039 --> 00:00:40.799
but if it's good PR
for the book.

17
00:00:40.823 --> 00:00:42.279
who cares if he's an ass?

18
00:00:42.303 --> 00:00:44.020
Unhand me!
I have a right to be here!

19
00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:45.760
Sorry. Norman.
no visitors allowed.

20
00:00:45.784 --> 00:00:47.719
As President of
Ms. Chandler's fan club.

21
00:00:47.743 --> 00:00:49.242
as well as
her official archivist.

22
00:00:49.266 --> 00:00:50.635
it is essential for me
to be here

23
00:00:50.659 --> 00:00:53.725
to document her appearance
on <i>Dean's Catch.</i>

24
00:00:53.749 --> 00:00:55.857
I have the proper credentials.

25
00:00:55.881 --> 00:00:57.120
You made that at home.

26
00:00:57.144 --> 00:00:58.382
Hmm.

27
00:00:58.406 --> 00:00:59.818
Allison! Oh...

28
00:00:59.842 --> 00:01:01.428
dear Allison. please.
tell this villain

29
00:01:01.452 --> 00:01:03.387
how I put my life in jeopardy
to save yours.

30
00:01:03.411 --> 00:01:04.953
It's okay. Noah.
He can stay.

31
00:01:04.977 --> 00:01:05.954
All right.

32
00:01:05.978 --> 00:01:07.763
Excuse me.

33
00:01:09.069 --> 00:01:10.721
They're ready
for you two inside.

34
00:01:13.856 --> 00:01:15.268
Ah! And here they are.

35
00:01:15.292 --> 00:01:16.139
-Hey.
-Hey.

36
00:01:16.163 --> 00:01:16.835
Hey.

37
00:01:16.859 --> 00:01:18.010
Hi. Nice to...

38
00:01:18.034 --> 00:01:20.143
Nice to...
It's good to...

39
00:01:20.167 --> 00:01:22.754
Yeah. so good to see you.
Detective Kerrigan.

40
00:01:22.778 --> 00:01:23.885
"Jack."

41
00:01:23.909 --> 00:01:24.886
I know.

42
00:01:24.910 --> 00:01:25.887
Okay.

43
00:01:25.911 --> 00:01:27.411
O-kay.

44
00:01:27.435 --> 00:01:28.629
I'm Andi Walker.

45
00:01:28.653 --> 00:01:30.153
and you already know
Allison Chandler.

46
00:01:30.177 --> 00:01:31.415
Yeah. all too well.

47
00:01:31.439 --> 00:01:33.460
We've always circled
the same harbor. haven't we. Al?

48
00:01:33.484 --> 00:01:35.071
Plenty of wind at our sails.
but. uh...

49
00:01:35.095 --> 00:01:36.225
never the right current.

50
00:01:37.314 --> 00:01:39.162
But this ship sailed
10 years ago...

51
00:01:39.186 --> 00:01:41.903
so I guess you're gonna
have to trim someone else's jib.

52
00:01:41.927 --> 00:01:43.209
if you know what I mean?

53
00:01:43.233 --> 00:01:44.384
I know what you mean.

54
00:01:44.408 --> 00:01:46.082
Well. we... are. uh.

55
00:01:46.106 --> 00:01:49.389
always happy to discuss
our exciting new project.

56
00:01:49.413 --> 00:01:51.783
And by "we."
I mean. Andi and I...

57
00:01:51.807 --> 00:01:52.871
-Mm-hmm.
-not Jack and I.

58
00:01:52.895 --> 00:01:55.178
not that there is
a "Jack and I" at all.

59
00:01:55.202 --> 00:01:57.464
but we've shared
a casual glass of wine.

60
00:01:58.727 --> 00:01:59.747
Jack is a detective.

61
00:01:59.771 --> 00:02:01.836
I think he knows that.

62
00:02:01.860 --> 00:02:03.099
Yeah.

63
00:02:03.123 --> 00:02:04.622
Thanks. uh. for being here.
Detective Kerrigan.

64
00:02:04.646 --> 00:02:05.623
Yeah. more the merrier.

65
00:02:05.647 --> 00:02:06.754
-Oh. we're merry!
-Yeah.

66
00:02:06.778 --> 00:02:08.016
Except when people get murdered.

67
00:02:08.040 --> 00:02:09.366
which they have...

68
00:02:09.390 --> 00:02:10.608
a lot.

69
00:02:11.957 --> 00:02:13.437
Are you high?

70
00:02:14.438 --> 00:02:15.894
Uh... okay.

71
00:02:15.918 --> 00:02:16.982
Why don't the three of you
sit on this side of the table?

72
00:02:17.006 --> 00:02:18.526
-That's a good idea.
-Yeah. let's go.

73
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:21.160
Ahem.

74
00:02:21.184 --> 00:02:22.901
Mocha soy whip...

75
00:02:22.925 --> 00:02:24.511
extra whip.

76
00:02:24.535 --> 00:02:26.905
Jules. you're a lifesaver.

77
00:02:26.929 --> 00:02:29.342
You know. Juliette's
more than just my co-host.

78
00:02:29.366 --> 00:02:30.865
She pretty much
does everything around here.

79
00:02:30.889 --> 00:02:31.997
Hmm.

80
00:02:32.021 --> 00:02:33.390
I draw the line
at picking up his laundry.

81
00:02:33.414 --> 00:02:34.869
But not at getting coffee.

82
00:02:34.893 --> 00:02:35.783
It's self-defense!

83
00:02:35.807 --> 00:02:37.655
Katherine says he's "a bear"

84
00:02:37.679 --> 00:02:39.178
if he doesn't get his java
in the morning.

85
00:02:39.202 --> 00:02:40.962
Who is Katherine?

86
00:02:40.986 --> 00:02:42.486
Oh. that's my beautiful wife.

87
00:02:42.510 --> 00:02:44.096
Juliette was her teacher's aide
in school.

88
00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:45.663
before the layoffs.

89
00:02:45.687 --> 00:02:48.100
You know. I used to
do all of this myself.

90
00:02:48.124 --> 00:02:50.972
and then. uh. as you know.
the podcast blew up. and. uh.

91
00:02:50.996 --> 00:02:53.215
well. I was
just stretched too thin.

92
00:02:54.391 --> 00:02:56.282
"Murderville. USA."
am I right. Al?

93
00:02:56.306 --> 00:02:57.370
Oh. I-I don't think
we should use that term.

94
00:02:57.394 --> 00:02:58.980
-Ah!
-So. uh...

95
00:02:59.004 --> 00:03:00.156
should we get started?

96
00:03:00.180 --> 00:03:01.418
Oh yeah.

97
00:03:01.442 --> 00:03:02.419
The hard-nosed detective.
chompin' at the bit...

98
00:03:02.443 --> 00:03:03.724
I like it. but hold your horse!

99
00:03:03.748 --> 00:03:05.117
We're just waiting
on one more guest.

100
00:03:05.141 --> 00:03:06.336
-Okay.
-Ah. sorry I'm late!

101
00:03:06.360 --> 00:03:07.796
And here she is!

102
00:03:09.667 --> 00:03:11.384
Uh. what is she doing here?

103
00:03:11.408 --> 00:03:12.733
Well. uh.
since we're talking about

104
00:03:12.757 --> 00:03:14.561
the recent string of murders
in Founders Cove.

105
00:03:14.585 --> 00:03:15.867
I thought it might be something

106
00:03:15.891 --> 00:03:17.695
if the honorary mayor
was here with us. too.

107
00:03:17.719 --> 00:03:19.067
Oh. it's something. all right.

108
00:03:20.417 --> 00:03:21.481
So shall we get started?

109
00:03:21.505 --> 00:03:22.724
Oh. yeah.

110
00:03:24.595 --> 00:03:26.965
Juliette?
Count it down. please.

111
00:03:26.989 --> 00:03:28.880
And ten. nine...

112
00:03:28.904 --> 00:03:30.186
Um. I'm thinking of
catching a movie tonight.

113
00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:31.752
if you wanted to join?

114
00:03:31.776 --> 00:03:34.712
I can't. We've got a schedule
to get this draft out.

115
00:03:34.736 --> 00:03:36.496
Four. three...

116
00:03:36.520 --> 00:03:39.020
Good morning. Founders Cove.

117
00:03:39.044 --> 00:03:41.022
and all our subscribers
around the world.

118
00:03:41.046 --> 00:03:42.285
I'm Dean Stark weather.

119
00:03:42.309 --> 00:03:45.549
and you are listening
to <i>Dean's Catch...</i>

120
00:03:45.573 --> 00:03:46.985
<i>caught ya!</i>

121
00:03:47.009 --> 00:03:49.292
A special treat today...
we are broadcasting live

122
00:03:49.316 --> 00:03:51.207
from the Founders Cove
Sheriff's Office.

123
00:03:51.231 --> 00:03:52.556
talking all things...
you guessed it...

124
00:03:52.580 --> 00:03:55.321
"Murderville. U.S. of A."

125
00:03:56.540 --> 00:03:58.126
What the heck?

126
00:03:58.150 --> 00:04:01.304
Now. as usual. my co-host.
Juliette Daestrom.

127
00:04:01.328 --> 00:04:03.349
will be feeding me
your live questions

128
00:04:03.373 --> 00:04:04.524
on the air.

129
00:04:04.548 --> 00:04:05.830
and I'm sure
you will have plenty.

130
00:04:05.854 --> 00:04:07.527
because. today. we are joined

131
00:04:07.551 --> 00:04:09.312
by Detective Jack Kerrigan.

132
00:04:09.336 --> 00:04:12.053
Also. we have Honorary Mayor
of Founders Cove.

133
00:04:12.077 --> 00:04:13.707
Connie Newsome...

134
00:04:13.731 --> 00:04:16.362
and we have somebody
who needs no introduction.

135
00:04:16.386 --> 00:04:18.930
award-winning author.
and local super-sleuth.

136
00:04:18.954 --> 00:04:21.237
Allison Chandler.

137
00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:23.500
Oh! And her sidekick.
"Ahn-drea" Walker.

138
00:04:23.524 --> 00:04:25.371
It's "Andrea."
and I'm not her sidekick.

139
00:04:25.395 --> 00:04:28.113
It's a pleasure
to be here. Dean.

140
00:04:28.137 --> 00:04:29.375
You're talking into the camera.

141
00:04:29.399 --> 00:04:30.681
Well. why don't we
kick things off

142
00:04:30.705 --> 00:04:32.639
by asking Detective Kerrigan
a question?

143
00:04:32.663 --> 00:04:33.901
Detective.

144
00:04:33.925 --> 00:04:36.904
you are the local
respected law enforcement here.

145
00:04:36.928 --> 00:04:38.428
but let's get honest.

146
00:04:38.452 --> 00:04:41.039
Having these two nosing-in
on your investigations.

147
00:04:41.063 --> 00:04:42.432
trying to take all your glory.

148
00:04:42.456 --> 00:04:45.391
well. that must just
stick in your craw. hmm?

149
00:04:45.415 --> 00:04:46.305
-What?
-Is that...

150
00:04:46.329 --> 00:04:47.480
-Is that a real question?
-Oh. come on!

151
00:04:47.504 --> 00:04:48.655
Dean...

152
00:04:48.679 --> 00:04:51.571
we have a message
from Carol in Watertown.

153
00:04:51.595 --> 00:04:52.790
who wants to know
how old Allie is.

154
00:04:52.814 --> 00:04:54.182
-Oh.
-Great question!

155
00:04:54.206 --> 00:04:55.271
Oh...

156
00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:58.099
Well. Carol...

157
00:04:58.123 --> 00:05:01.364
<i>I'm old enough to know better
than to answer that question.</i>

158
00:05:01.388 --> 00:05:03.017
<i>But you're never
too old to exploit</i>

159
00:05:03.041 --> 00:05:06.238
<i>the public's taste for murder.
am I right. Allie?</i>

160
00:05:06.262 --> 00:05:07.370
<i>Uh. I'm not exploiting anyone.</i>

161
00:05:07.394 --> 00:05:09.415
<i>The public loves mysteries.</i>

162
00:05:09.439 --> 00:05:11.112
<i>and. yes. the stakes
can be life and death.</i>

163
00:05:11.136 --> 00:05:12.766
<i>but they have to be.</i>

164
00:05:12.790 --> 00:05:14.681
<i>otherwise. the reader won't
care what happens.</i>

165
00:05:14.705 --> 00:05:16.074
Katherine?

166
00:05:16.098 --> 00:05:18.142
Is everything okay?

167
00:05:25.716 --> 00:05:29.348
Can we please
do without the sound effects?

168
00:05:29.372 --> 00:05:32.220
If I can jump in here. Dean...

169
00:05:32.244 --> 00:05:34.353
it is true that we had
a string of tragedies

170
00:05:34.377 --> 00:05:35.398
here. at Founders Cove.

171
00:05:35.422 --> 00:05:37.661
It is also true
that. without these two.

172
00:05:37.685 --> 00:05:39.402
some of those killers
would still be on the loose.

173
00:05:39.426 --> 00:05:41.665
But I think maybe
this town would be safer

174
00:05:41.689 --> 00:05:42.927
if the police
didn't have to deal with.

175
00:05:42.951 --> 00:05:44.407
Cagney and Lacey over here

176
00:05:44.431 --> 00:05:45.538
getting in the way
in the first place!

177
00:05:45.562 --> 00:05:46.757
Who's Cagney and Lacey?

178
00:05:46.781 --> 00:05:48.106
Okay. I'll explain that
to you later.

179
00:05:48.130 --> 00:05:49.107
You take that back!

180
00:05:49.131 --> 00:05:50.413
I think it's outrageous

181
00:05:50.437 --> 00:05:51.588
that they're using
the recent tragedies

182
00:05:51.612 --> 00:05:53.198
to shamelessly sell books.

183
00:05:53.222 --> 00:05:54.068
<i>Caught ya!</i>

184
00:05:54.092 --> 00:05:55.635
You want to talk
about shameless?

185
00:05:55.659 --> 00:05:56.723
"Mayor Newsome" over there.

186
00:05:56.747 --> 00:05:57.942
she tried to write off
breast implants

187
00:05:57.966 --> 00:05:59.030
-as a campaign expense!
-Okay. that's...

188
00:05:59.054 --> 00:06:00.031
Ohh!

189
00:06:00.055 --> 00:06:01.554
That was a rumor!

190
00:06:01.578 --> 00:06:02.555
It's misappropriation of funds!

191
00:06:02.579 --> 00:06:04.059
-We don't need that.
-It's not true.

192
00:06:05.408 --> 00:06:07.343
Excuse me. what are you doing?

193
00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:08.822
We're in the middle
of a live podcast right now!

194
00:06:08.846 --> 00:06:11.042
If you've got something to say.
say it to us live!

195
00:06:11.066 --> 00:06:12.783
I don't think
that's a good idea.

196
00:06:12.807 --> 00:06:14.393
Look. that's what
journalism's all about.

197
00:06:14.417 --> 00:06:15.977
when it's live...
you just come and y...

198
00:06:20.336 --> 00:06:21.487
What?

199
00:06:21.511 --> 00:06:23.489
I'm so sorry.

200
00:06:23.513 --> 00:06:24.513
Oh. my God...

201
00:06:26.124 --> 00:06:27.101
Oh. my God!

202
00:06:27.125 --> 00:06:28.233
Uh. stop...

203
00:06:28.257 --> 00:06:30.085
stop the podcast.

204
00:06:34.089 --> 00:06:36.178
My-My wife
just committed suicide.

205
00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:58.568
How could she do this?

206
00:06:58.592 --> 00:07:00.047
Dean...

207
00:07:00.071 --> 00:07:02.920
any recent changes
to Katherine's mood or behavior?

208
00:07:02.944 --> 00:07:04.922
She was on some new meds.

209
00:07:04.946 --> 00:07:06.706
Look. I thought
they were working.

210
00:07:06.730 --> 00:07:08.752
I don't know! Maybe
I-I could've done something

211
00:07:08.776 --> 00:07:09.753
to stop this. you know?

212
00:07:09.777 --> 00:07:10.928
You can't blame yourself.

213
00:07:10.952 --> 00:07:13.365
Look. is there somewhere
you can stay tonight?

214
00:07:13.389 --> 00:07:15.149
Someone we can call for you?

215
00:07:15.173 --> 00:07:18.718
Um. no.
No. no. I-I need to be alone.

216
00:07:18.742 --> 00:07:20.633
I'll just go to a hotel
for a few days.

217
00:07:20.657 --> 00:07:22.679
-We'll give you a ride.
-Okay.

218
00:07:22.703 --> 00:07:24.985
Dean. I am so sorry.

219
00:07:25.009 --> 00:07:28.075
No. no. I'm sorry.
for what I said on the show.

220
00:07:28.099 --> 00:07:30.948
I-I didn't mean anything by it.
It was just for the show. okay?

221
00:07:30.972 --> 00:07:31.949
Take him where he wants.

222
00:07:31.973 --> 00:07:33.408
Yes. sir.

223
00:07:34.671 --> 00:07:38.346
Katherine Stark weather
was a second-grade teacher.

224
00:07:38.370 --> 00:07:40.087
Everyone loved her.

225
00:07:40.111 --> 00:07:42.549
Did she leave a note?

226
00:07:44.028 --> 00:07:46.117
No note.

227
00:08:04.658 --> 00:08:06.137
Prescription sedative.

228
00:08:07.965 --> 00:08:11.118
She must've drugged herself
so she wouldn't back out.

229
00:08:11.142 --> 00:08:12.511
sat on the bar stool.

230
00:08:12.535 --> 00:08:14.252
put the noose around her neck.

231
00:08:14.276 --> 00:08:16.820
pushed the button
on the garage remote.

232
00:08:16.844 --> 00:08:18.256
and then. lights out.

233
00:08:18.280 --> 00:08:19.736
Yeah.

234
00:08:19.760 --> 00:08:21.825
The neighbor. Donna Falconer.
saw the garage door open.

235
00:08:21.849 --> 00:08:24.567
She said the deceased was
still moving when she got here.

236
00:08:24.591 --> 00:08:27.680
She tried to help.
but it was too late.

237
00:08:28.769 --> 00:08:29.963
Well. guess that's it. then.

238
00:08:29.987 --> 00:08:31.032
Thanks. guys.

239
00:08:32.250 --> 00:08:33.924
Wait.

240
00:08:33.948 --> 00:08:36.492
Why is CSU leaving
without collecting evidence?

241
00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:37.754
Because this was a suicide.

242
00:08:37.778 --> 00:08:39.519
The neighbor saw
the whole thing happen.

243
00:08:40.694 --> 00:08:42.759
There's no sign
of foul play here.

244
00:08:42.783 --> 00:08:44.871
Come on.

245
00:08:56.666 --> 00:08:57.904
You do realize

246
00:08:57.928 --> 00:09:00.646
you didn't say one word
that entire car ride?

247
00:09:00.670 --> 00:09:01.691
So?

248
00:09:01.715 --> 00:09:03.170
So. I know that face...

249
00:09:03.194 --> 00:09:04.476
it's the face you make

250
00:09:04.500 --> 00:09:06.060
when you think
something doesn't add up.

251
00:09:07.503 --> 00:09:08.915
Okay. in every crime.

252
00:09:08.939 --> 00:09:11.918
there's something
that feels just off...

253
00:09:11.942 --> 00:09:14.660
but this one. it's flawless.

254
00:09:14.684 --> 00:09:16.880
A-A wife commits suicide

255
00:09:16.904 --> 00:09:18.664
while millions of people

256
00:09:18.688 --> 00:09:20.666
are watching and listening
to her husband

257
00:09:20.690 --> 00:09:21.928
on a podcast.

258
00:09:21.952 --> 00:09:24.670
I could not have written
a better alibi.

259
00:09:24.694 --> 00:09:26.498
That's because Dean
doesn't need an alibi.

260
00:09:26.522 --> 00:09:28.021
There's no crime. Allie.

261
00:09:28.045 --> 00:09:29.675
His wife committed suicide.

262
00:09:29.699 --> 00:09:31.068
You saw Dean...

263
00:09:31.092 --> 00:09:32.722
<i>the new tattoo on his hand.</i>

264
00:09:32.746 --> 00:09:34.288
<i>the whitened teeth...</i>

265
00:09:34.312 --> 00:09:35.855
that's a husband
ready for change.

266
00:09:35.879 --> 00:09:37.030
Statistically.

267
00:09:37.054 --> 00:09:39.753
that is <i>the</i> most dangerous kind
of husband.

268
00:09:43.147 --> 00:09:45.386
Oh. it's probably
the window cleaners.

269
00:09:45.410 --> 00:09:47.020
I'll tell 'em to start out back.

270
00:09:48.196 --> 00:09:49.892
What?

271
00:09:51.155 --> 00:09:52.916
Hi! What. no call?

272
00:09:52.940 --> 00:09:54.395
Ahh! I wanted to surprise ya!

273
00:09:54.419 --> 00:09:56.267
You did!

274
00:09:56.291 --> 00:09:57.529
Allie. this is my dad. Kevin.

275
00:09:57.553 --> 00:09:58.878
Oh!

276
00:09:58.902 --> 00:10:01.315
Well. I guess you're not here
to wash my windows. then.

277
00:10:01.339 --> 00:10:03.317
No. but I'm happy to pitch in.

278
00:10:03.341 --> 00:10:05.363
Oh!
Uh. Allison Chandler.

279
00:10:05.387 --> 00:10:06.538
So nice to meet you.

280
00:10:06.562 --> 00:10:07.583
Allie. I know.

281
00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:09.497
I've heard all about you.

282
00:10:09.521 --> 00:10:10.890
Oh. So what brings you
to Founders Cove?

283
00:10:10.914 --> 00:10:12.500
I got a job up in Portland.

284
00:10:12.524 --> 00:10:14.415
but I wanted to stop
and see Andi on my way.

285
00:10:14.439 --> 00:10:16.766
I do. uh.
construction. remodeling.

286
00:10:16.790 --> 00:10:18.550
You must be pretty handsy.

287
00:10:18.574 --> 00:10:21.248
I mean. handy...
you... must be handy.

288
00:10:21.272 --> 00:10:24.730
I'm pretty good with my hands.
or so I've been told.

289
00:10:24.754 --> 00:10:26.732
First. ew! Second.
how long are you staying?

290
00:10:26.756 --> 00:10:27.864
Uh. just overnight.

291
00:10:27.888 --> 00:10:29.256
I gotta go into town.
find a hotel room.

292
00:10:29.280 --> 00:10:30.214
Oh. don't be silly.

293
00:10:30.238 --> 00:10:31.694
There's a guest room
in the main house.

294
00:10:31.718 --> 00:10:33.173
The main house guest room?

295
00:10:33.197 --> 00:10:34.784
Are you sure your butler
won't be upset?

296
00:10:34.808 --> 00:10:35.872
Oh. he sleeps in the shed.

297
00:10:35.896 --> 00:10:36.612
Ah.

298
00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:38.570
I insist.

299
00:10:38.594 --> 00:10:41.094
On one condition...
that you let me cook dinner.

300
00:10:41.118 --> 00:10:42.618
And you... you cook?

301
00:10:42.642 --> 00:10:43.662
Yeah.

302
00:10:43.686 --> 00:10:45.403
Well. then. it's settled.

303
00:10:45.427 --> 00:10:47.274
Andi will show you
where your room is.

304
00:10:47.298 --> 00:10:50.103
and I'm gonna
leave you two to catch up.

305
00:10:50.127 --> 00:10:52.453
I'm just gonna go run an errand.
I'll see you later.

306
00:10:52.477 --> 00:10:54.064
Okay.

307
00:10:54.088 --> 00:10:55.176
I'll be right back.

308
00:10:56.351 --> 00:10:57.937
I know what you're doing!

309
00:10:57.961 --> 00:11:01.158
I am not doing anything
except getting in my car.

310
00:11:01.182 --> 00:11:02.072
You're gonna go back
to the Starkweathers' garage.

311
00:11:02.096 --> 00:11:03.073
aren't you?

312
00:11:03.097 --> 00:11:04.161
I'm gonna go talk
to her neighbor.

313
00:11:04.185 --> 00:11:05.205
Then I'm coming with you.

314
00:11:05.229 --> 00:11:07.033
No. you're not.
You've got company.

315
00:11:07.057 --> 00:11:08.339
Dad. front door's open!

316
00:11:08.363 --> 00:11:09.645
The guest room's
on the second floor.

317
00:11:09.669 --> 00:11:11.671
I'll be back in an hour. okay?

318
00:11:15.022 --> 00:11:16.937
Let's go!

319
00:11:17.938 --> 00:11:19.350
It's such a shame.

320
00:11:19.374 --> 00:11:21.439
Katherine was
a wonderful spirit.

321
00:11:21.463 --> 00:11:23.441
Do you have any idea what
could've made her so desperate?

322
00:11:23.465 --> 00:11:25.356
Not a clue.

323
00:11:25.380 --> 00:11:28.054
How was her marriage to Dean?

324
00:11:28.078 --> 00:11:31.449
Well. it wasn't perfect.
but what marriage is.

325
00:11:31.473 --> 00:11:32.668
if you know what I mean?

326
00:11:32.692 --> 00:11:33.973
Oh. she knows.

327
00:11:33.997 --> 00:11:35.366
Ahem.

328
00:11:35.390 --> 00:11:37.411
I... I shouldn't gossip.
but. the other day.

329
00:11:37.435 --> 00:11:38.935
I did see a woman
visit the house.

330
00:11:38.959 --> 00:11:42.416
Katherine was
at a parent-teacher conference.

331
00:11:42.440 --> 00:11:45.289
Pretty hair. nice gams.

332
00:11:45.313 --> 00:11:47.944
So much for
Dean's "loyal husband" act.

333
00:11:47.968 --> 00:11:50.598
Yeah. maybe it pushed
poor Katherine over the edge.

334
00:11:50.622 --> 00:11:53.601
Or maybe this woman was
collecting money for charity

335
00:11:53.625 --> 00:11:55.865
or looking for a lost pet.

336
00:11:55.889 --> 00:11:57.867
You wouldn't happen
to have a way

337
00:11:57.891 --> 00:12:00.696
to get into
their garage. do you?

338
00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:01.827
Just to see
if we missed something

339
00:12:01.851 --> 00:12:03.002
that might explain
what happened?

340
00:12:03.026 --> 00:12:04.003
Oh. that's right.

341
00:12:04.027 --> 00:12:06.223
You're that famous novelist

342
00:12:06.247 --> 00:12:07.441
and you're the sidekick.

343
00:12:07.465 --> 00:12:09.269
"Writing partner."

344
00:12:09.293 --> 00:12:12.142
I water Katherine's plants
when they're away.

345
00:12:12.166 --> 00:12:15.081
I'll grab you the key
to the back door.

346
00:12:20.870 --> 00:12:22.089
All right...

347
00:12:23.873 --> 00:12:25.198
You be Katherine.

348
00:12:25.222 --> 00:12:27.113
What? No! You be Katherine.

349
00:12:27.137 --> 00:12:28.898
No. Katherine is short.
I'm tall.

350
00:12:28.922 --> 00:12:30.203
Come on!

351
00:12:30.227 --> 00:12:31.727
Fine. but I am not putting
that noose around my neck.

352
00:12:31.751 --> 00:12:33.206
Fair.

353
00:12:33.230 --> 00:12:34.251
Here.

354
00:12:34.275 --> 00:12:37.341
All right. so... hmm.

355
00:12:37.365 --> 00:12:40.387
Katherine downs
an overdose of pills.

356
00:12:40.411 --> 00:12:43.086
Her mind relaxes. but...

357
00:12:43.110 --> 00:12:44.914
she is conscious enough

358
00:12:44.938 --> 00:12:46.306
to press the button
on the remote.

359
00:12:46.330 --> 00:12:48.724
and seal her fate.

360
00:12:50.160 --> 00:12:51.616
She presses the button
on the remote

361
00:12:51.640 --> 00:12:52.791
to seal her fate!

362
00:12:52.815 --> 00:12:54.271
Would you press the damn button?

363
00:12:54.295 --> 00:12:55.751
I did!
It doesn't work!

364
00:12:55.775 --> 00:12:56.926
Let me see that.

365
00:12:56.950 --> 00:12:58.710
Maybe it broke
when she dropped it.

366
00:12:58.734 --> 00:13:00.040
Well...

367
00:13:01.215 --> 00:13:02.322
Huh!

368
00:13:02.346 --> 00:13:04.803
Batteries are corroded.

369
00:13:04.827 --> 00:13:06.718
So...
the remote wasn't working.

370
00:13:06.742 --> 00:13:09.416
which means
she didn't commit suicide.

371
00:13:09.440 --> 00:13:11.027
Or...
when Katherine pressed it.

372
00:13:11.051 --> 00:13:12.898
it was the last charge it had
before it died.

373
00:13:12.922 --> 00:13:13.943
and she did commit suicide.

374
00:13:13.967 --> 00:13:15.466
Or...

375
00:13:15.490 --> 00:13:17.120
maybe she didn't
open the garage door...

376
00:13:17.144 --> 00:13:19.775
someone else opened it.

377
00:13:19.799 --> 00:13:21.602
We've gotta talk to Dean.
see what he has to say.

378
00:13:21.626 --> 00:13:23.517
He was sitting
next to us on the podcast!

379
00:13:23.541 --> 00:13:26.390
There's no way
that he opened this garage door.

380
00:13:26.414 --> 00:13:28.131
I just want to ask him
some questions.

381
00:13:28.155 --> 00:13:30.437
Can we please give this man
some time to process?

382
00:13:30.461 --> 00:13:32.811
Get him some flowers?

383
00:13:41.690 --> 00:13:43.320
Allison Chandler.

384
00:13:43.344 --> 00:13:44.756
what can I do for you?

385
00:13:44.780 --> 00:13:46.062
We wanted to bring you these.

386
00:13:46.086 --> 00:13:47.150
Ah.

387
00:13:47.174 --> 00:13:50.196
That's sweet. Thanks.

388
00:13:50.220 --> 00:13:52.416
Now. if you don't mind.
I'd like to be alone.

389
00:13:52.440 --> 00:13:53.765
Yup. we understand. Come on!

390
00:13:53.789 --> 00:13:55.854
You know. I had
one teensy. tiny question

391
00:13:55.878 --> 00:13:57.900
about your garage door.

392
00:13:57.924 --> 00:13:59.336
Oh...

393
00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:01.033
I thought you said
you wanted to be alone?

394
00:14:01.057 --> 00:14:02.687
That's just. uh.
one of those phantom flushes.

395
00:14:02.711 --> 00:14:04.712
I should have jiggled
the handle or something.

396
00:14:06.062 --> 00:14:08.107
You can come out now. Juliette!

397
00:14:13.678 --> 00:14:14.830
Look.

398
00:14:14.854 --> 00:14:16.919
We all grieve in different ways.

399
00:14:16.943 --> 00:14:18.529
Oh. I bet you two have "grieved"

400
00:14:18.553 --> 00:14:20.226
at least twice already today.

401
00:14:20.250 --> 00:14:22.054
How'd you know it was Juliette?

402
00:14:22.078 --> 00:14:23.490
Well. aside from
the proximity effect...

403
00:14:23.514 --> 00:14:26.754
where men tend to cheat
with women they work with...

404
00:14:26.778 --> 00:14:29.845
<i>Juliette grazed his arm
when she brought him coffee.</i>

405
00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:32.282
<i>He inhaled as she delivered it.</i>

406
00:14:32.306 --> 00:14:33.674
trying to smell her perfume.

407
00:14:33.698 --> 00:14:35.285
Your neighbor

408
00:14:35.309 --> 00:14:37.026
said that she saw
a woman at your house

409
00:14:37.050 --> 00:14:38.375
Wednesday night.

410
00:14:38.399 --> 00:14:40.290
while your wife was
at parent-teacher conferences.

411
00:14:40.314 --> 00:14:42.161
so I'm guessing it was Juliette?

412
00:14:42.185 --> 00:14:43.902
-No.
-No.

413
00:14:43.926 --> 00:14:47.688
I was out of town on Wednesday.

414
00:14:47.712 --> 00:14:49.212
Jules. I can explain everything.

415
00:14:49.236 --> 00:14:50.387
Just give me a... uh...

416
00:14:50.411 --> 00:14:51.867
I can explain. Jules!

417
00:14:51.891 --> 00:14:52.998
Jules!

418
00:14:53.022 --> 00:14:55.218
If the lady with the "nice gams"

419
00:14:55.242 --> 00:14:57.046
is not Juliette. who is she?

420
00:14:57.070 --> 00:14:58.482
That's none of your business!

421
00:14:58.506 --> 00:14:59.744
Oh. really?

422
00:14:59.768 --> 00:15:01.572
Okay. well. I was
gonna ease into this. see.

423
00:15:01.596 --> 00:15:04.270
but it's clear
that you've moved on. so...

424
00:15:04.294 --> 00:15:08.144
the batteries in this remote
are dead.

425
00:15:08.168 --> 00:15:10.363
which means your wife could not
have opened the garage door

426
00:15:10.387 --> 00:15:11.582
with it.

427
00:15:11.606 --> 00:15:12.931
Somebody else must've done it.

428
00:15:12.955 --> 00:15:14.019
and we all know

429
00:15:14.043 --> 00:15:16.630
that Juliette was with us
at the podcast.

430
00:15:16.654 --> 00:15:20.199
Maybe this other mystery woman
is someone we should talk to.

431
00:15:20.223 --> 00:15:21.200
Look.

432
00:15:21.224 --> 00:15:23.724
My wife was depressed.

433
00:15:23.748 --> 00:15:25.596
I wish I could've helped her.

434
00:15:25.620 --> 00:15:27.685
but I couldn't.

435
00:15:27.709 --> 00:15:29.579
Now leave me alone.

436
00:15:34.629 --> 00:15:36.085
No.

437
00:15:36.109 --> 00:15:37.738
We just want to talk.

438
00:15:37.762 --> 00:15:39.001
I don't!

439
00:15:39.025 --> 00:15:40.916
Juliette. we know
you've done anything wrong...

440
00:15:40.940 --> 00:15:42.134
except adultery.

441
00:15:42.158 --> 00:15:43.222
and sleeping with a man

442
00:15:43.246 --> 00:15:44.571
on the day his wife
committed suicide...

443
00:15:44.595 --> 00:15:46.051
Look!

444
00:15:46.075 --> 00:15:48.184
I feel terrible.

445
00:15:48.208 --> 00:15:50.534
I mean. I used to work
with Katherine.

446
00:15:50.558 --> 00:15:51.970
We were friends.

447
00:15:51.994 --> 00:15:54.146
This other woman
that was at the house.

448
00:15:54.170 --> 00:15:55.610
seems like you might know
who she is.

449
00:15:56.999 --> 00:15:59.064
I know
she's been calling him lately.

450
00:15:59.088 --> 00:16:00.326
I checked his phone.

451
00:16:00.350 --> 00:16:01.917
Anyone we know?

452
00:16:03.136 --> 00:16:06.399
She was sitting right across
from you on the podcast.

453
00:16:09.533 --> 00:16:12.034
I was as surprised as anyone.

454
00:16:12.058 --> 00:16:13.513
Not that I knew Dean
and his wife well.

455
00:16:13.537 --> 00:16:14.645
but in my line of work.

456
00:16:14.669 --> 00:16:16.560
you hear all the latest gossip.

457
00:16:16.584 --> 00:16:19.519
As far as I knew.
they were a happy couple.

458
00:16:19.543 --> 00:16:21.632
So why did you go over
to his house the other night?

459
00:16:23.330 --> 00:16:24.916
It's not what it sounds like.

460
00:16:24.940 --> 00:16:26.048
We're just friends.

461
00:16:26.072 --> 00:16:27.658
Dean's not just a "friend"

462
00:16:27.682 --> 00:16:29.616
if you visit him late at night

463
00:16:29.640 --> 00:16:32.861
while his wife is at
a parent-teacher conference.

464
00:16:34.515 --> 00:16:35.927
All right.

465
00:16:35.951 --> 00:16:37.233
We were seeing each other...

466
00:16:37.257 --> 00:16:38.277
Mm.

467
00:16:38.301 --> 00:16:39.800
Romantically.

468
00:16:39.824 --> 00:16:40.845
Is that a crime?

469
00:16:40.869 --> 00:16:41.933
There is a chance

470
00:16:41.957 --> 00:16:43.195
that Katherine
did not commit suicide.

471
00:16:43.219 --> 00:16:44.370
A small chance.

472
00:16:44.394 --> 00:16:45.806
But her neighbor saw her do it.

473
00:16:45.830 --> 00:16:48.679
Again. there is <i>a chance</i>
that it could have been staged.

474
00:16:48.703 --> 00:16:50.637
<i>Again.</i> a very small chance.

475
00:16:50.661 --> 00:16:54.206
Not a small chance...
a regular. full-size chance

476
00:16:54.230 --> 00:16:57.296
that someone killed Katherine.
and staged it as a suicide.

477
00:16:57.320 --> 00:16:59.995
I was with both of you
at the police station

478
00:17:00.019 --> 00:17:01.518
when all of this happened.

479
00:17:01.542 --> 00:17:03.607
so I don't see how any of this
has anything to do with me.

480
00:17:03.631 --> 00:17:05.130
I-I can't think
about this right now.

481
00:17:05.154 --> 00:17:07.113
I have to be in Hair and Makeup
in 20 minutes.

482
00:17:08.331 --> 00:17:09.811
Pfft.

483
00:17:10.986 --> 00:17:12.833
-Okay.
-Ahem.

484
00:17:12.857 --> 00:17:15.053
Another perfect alibi.

485
00:17:15.077 --> 00:17:16.315
What now?

486
00:17:16.339 --> 00:17:16.968
Well...

487
00:17:16.992 --> 00:17:18.187
-Oh!
-Oh.

488
00:17:18.211 --> 00:17:19.318
Oh...!

489
00:17:19.342 --> 00:17:20.276
I thought you two
would be writing.

490
00:17:20.300 --> 00:17:21.407
Oh. we were.

491
00:17:21.431 --> 00:17:23.322
Yeah. we were... we were
hard at work.

492
00:17:23.346 --> 00:17:25.672
which is why
I couldn't go to the movies.

493
00:17:25.696 --> 00:17:27.370
and then we got a surprise
visitor... Andi's dad...

494
00:17:27.394 --> 00:17:29.024
-Oh!
-and now we came here

495
00:17:29.048 --> 00:17:31.243
to get some pie. for dessert.

496
00:17:31.267 --> 00:17:33.419
Yeah.
Unfortunately. they have no pie.

497
00:17:33.443 --> 00:17:35.508
But we can get pie at Rosa's!

498
00:17:35.532 --> 00:17:36.683
-Mm.
-I like pie.

499
00:17:36.707 --> 00:17:38.381
I like pie. too.

500
00:17:38.405 --> 00:17:41.514
Okay. well.
enjoy your visitor...

501
00:17:41.538 --> 00:17:43.038
and your pie.

502
00:17:43.062 --> 00:17:45.605
We will.

503
00:17:45.629 --> 00:17:47.999
What's going on with you two?

504
00:17:48.023 --> 00:17:50.436
-Absolutely nothing! Okay?
-Uh-huh. okay.

505
00:17:50.460 --> 00:17:51.568
Hi there.
are you ready to order?

506
00:17:51.592 --> 00:17:54.073
Hi. Are you really out of pie?

507
00:17:57.902 --> 00:18:01.143
♪ Like a worn-out recording

508
00:18:01.167 --> 00:18:03.971
♪ Of your favorite song

509
00:18:03.995 --> 00:18:06.800
♪ So while she lay there
sleeping ♪

510
00:18:06.824 --> 00:18:09.064
♪ I read the paper in bed...

511
00:18:09.088 --> 00:18:11.283
Okay. you can stop
singing now. Dad.

512
00:18:11.307 --> 00:18:14.025
♪ And in the personal columns

513
00:18:14.049 --> 00:18:16.506
♪ There was this letter
I read ♪

514
00:18:16.530 --> 00:18:18.986
♪ If you like Piña Coladas

515
00:18:19.010 --> 00:18:20.814
No. Don't.

516
00:18:20.838 --> 00:18:23.382
♪ And getting caught
in the rain ♪

517
00:18:23.406 --> 00:18:27.082
♪ If you're not into yoga

518
00:18:27.106 --> 00:18:30.172
♪ If you have half a brain

519
00:18:30.196 --> 00:18:33.218
♪ If you like
making love at midnight ♪

520
00:18:33.242 --> 00:18:37.396
♪ In the dunes of the Cape

521
00:18:37.420 --> 00:18:41.096
♪ I'm the love
that you've looked for ♪

522
00:18:41.120 --> 00:18:44.078
♪ Come with me and escape

523
00:18:45.167 --> 00:18:46.927
Mm-hmm. Great.

524
00:18:46.951 --> 00:18:49.495
Oh. it was. uh. mid-'80s.

525
00:18:49.519 --> 00:18:52.585
I'm building these bookshelves
in Laurel Canyon for a guy.

526
00:18:52.609 --> 00:18:54.848
and he's got guitars everywhere.

527
00:18:54.872 --> 00:18:56.546
I mean.
they're all over the house.

528
00:18:56.570 --> 00:18:58.939
It turns out.
it is Eddie freakin' Van Halen.

529
00:18:58.963 --> 00:19:00.854
-No!
-And he's got

530
00:19:00.878 --> 00:19:03.074
friends coming over.
and they start shredding.

531
00:19:03.098 --> 00:19:04.641
and they are just going off.
and it was... it was crazy.

532
00:19:04.665 --> 00:19:06.512
It was the... the '80s.

533
00:19:06.536 --> 00:19:09.733
Everybody had Camembert
and cocaine in their fridge.

534
00:19:09.757 --> 00:19:12.280
Well. here's
to being young and foolish.

535
00:19:14.501 --> 00:19:16.914
Okay. that's it for me.

536
00:19:16.938 --> 00:19:18.505
-'Night.
-'Night.

537
00:19:19.549 --> 00:19:21.397
Goodnight.

538
00:19:21.421 --> 00:19:23.486
Mm-hmm.

539
00:19:23.510 --> 00:19:25.879
There's nothing better
than embarrassing your kid.

540
00:19:25.903 --> 00:19:27.143
Oh. I absolutely live for that.

541
00:19:28.036 --> 00:19:29.645
-You want...
-Oh. yes. please.

542
00:19:31.648 --> 00:19:33.583
You know. she's pretty lucky
to have you as a dad.

543
00:19:33.607 --> 00:19:35.106
She's pretty lucky to have
a partner in crime like you.

544
00:19:35.130 --> 00:19:36.847
Oh. I don't know about that...

545
00:19:36.871 --> 00:19:39.328
sometimes. I think
she wants to murder me.

546
00:19:39.352 --> 00:19:42.113
Well.
we've had our ups and downs.

547
00:19:42.137 --> 00:19:45.812
This whole "Mr. Mom" thing.
it didn't come easy.

548
00:19:45.836 --> 00:19:47.553
I can relate.

549
00:19:47.577 --> 00:19:50.774
I'm still trying to figure out
the whole "Mrs. Dad" thing.

550
00:19:50.798 --> 00:19:51.905
Ah.

551
00:19:51.929 --> 00:19:54.038
It's like being
two parents at once.

552
00:19:54.062 --> 00:19:56.736
You give twice the love.
you feel twice the pain.

553
00:19:56.760 --> 00:19:58.434
Thank you.

554
00:19:58.458 --> 00:20:00.871
Well. I'm no writer. but...

555
00:20:00.895 --> 00:20:02.873
I see why
they pay you the big bucks.

556
00:20:02.897 --> 00:20:05.484
That is the wine talking.

557
00:20:05.508 --> 00:20:07.182
Well. let's keep it coming.

558
00:20:07.206 --> 00:20:09.250
Mm.

559
00:20:10.557 --> 00:20:13.318
Oh. I love this song.

560
00:20:13.342 --> 00:20:14.754
Mm. Me too.

561
00:20:14.778 --> 00:20:16.475
Mm-hmm?

562
00:20:19.653 --> 00:20:23.046
♪ You've got
this boy believin'... ♪

563
00:20:24.745 --> 00:20:27.790
♪ It's all coming true...

564
00:20:30.316 --> 00:20:31.293
Hi.

565
00:20:31.317 --> 00:20:32.511
This okay?

566
00:20:32.535 --> 00:20:34.406
Yeah.

567
00:20:37.366 --> 00:20:39.475
♪ ...Nothing to do

568
00:20:39.499 --> 00:20:43.328
♪ So I'll be spendin'
all my time... ♪

569
00:20:44.678 --> 00:20:47.984
♪ Gettin' lazy with you

570
00:20:51.293 --> 00:20:54.904
♪ I wanna get lazy with you

571
00:20:57.647 --> 00:21:00.214
♪ Lazy with you

572
00:21:03.871 --> 00:21:05.240
Good morning.

573
00:21:05.264 --> 00:21:07.720
Morning.

574
00:21:07.744 --> 00:21:08.982
Wow...

575
00:21:09.006 --> 00:21:11.898
hey. hey. hey!
Whoa. ho. whoa. Don Juan!

576
00:21:11.922 --> 00:21:13.857
Your daughter lives here. remember?

577
00:21:13.881 --> 00:21:16.599
Well. it'd take a meteor
to wake her before 10:00.

578
00:21:16.623 --> 00:21:18.383
Besides. she's way out
in the guest house.

579
00:21:18.407 --> 00:21:20.429
What is on the menu?

580
00:21:20.453 --> 00:21:22.387
We got pumpkin-spice pancakes.

581
00:21:22.411 --> 00:21:25.782
Ooh. yum! I've got
some maple syrup somewhere.

582
00:21:25.806 --> 00:21:26.957
No whipped cream?

583
00:21:26.981 --> 00:21:28.785
Behave!

584
00:21:28.809 --> 00:21:30.352
That's not what you said
last night.

585
00:21:30.376 --> 00:21:32.202
Ho!

586
00:21:37.252 --> 00:21:38.577
Morning. Dad.

587
00:21:38.601 --> 00:21:40.927
Hey... kiddo! Uh...

588
00:21:40.951 --> 00:21:42.102
You're up early.

589
00:21:42.126 --> 00:21:43.103
You're never up early.

590
00:21:43.127 --> 00:21:44.999
Yeah. Laundry.

591
00:21:46.783 --> 00:21:47.891
Are these pumpkin-spice
pancakes?

592
00:21:47.915 --> 00:21:49.196
Yup. Mm-hmm.

593
00:21:49.220 --> 00:21:51.851
My favorite!
Oh. my God. I'll get the syrup.

594
00:21:51.875 --> 00:21:53.113
Nope! Wait. You don't
have to do that because. uh...

595
00:21:53.137 --> 00:21:54.400
It's okay. I know where it is.

596
00:21:55.444 --> 00:21:56.489
Oh!

597
00:21:57.707 --> 00:21:59.468
Uh... okay.

598
00:21:59.492 --> 00:22:00.686
What the hell are you wearing?

599
00:22:00.710 --> 00:22:02.122
Syrup?

600
00:22:02.146 --> 00:22:04.255
I repeat...
what the hell are you wearing?

601
00:22:04.279 --> 00:22:07.737
Oh. it's. um.
it's a Klaus Von Klaus.

602
00:22:07.761 --> 00:22:11.697
Mm. it's a kimono.
and you never wear kimonos.

603
00:22:11.721 --> 00:22:14.333
I love kimonos.

604
00:22:16.117 --> 00:22:17.161
Did you two...?

605
00:22:18.119 --> 00:22:19.749
Hmm.

606
00:22:19.773 --> 00:22:20.967
Oh. my God. you did.

607
00:22:20.991 --> 00:22:22.099
Oh. my God. you did!

608
00:22:22.123 --> 00:22:23.622
-W-We can explain...
-No!

609
00:22:23.646 --> 00:22:25.494
No! Do not explain!

610
00:22:25.518 --> 00:22:27.104
It's a perfectly natural thing
when two people...

611
00:22:27.128 --> 00:22:29.324
Oh. my God. stop talking!
You're saying the worst words

612
00:22:29.348 --> 00:22:30.629
I've ever heard! Ugh!

613
00:22:30.653 --> 00:22:31.674
Let me get that.

614
00:22:31.698 --> 00:22:32.936
No. I got it!

615
00:22:32.960 --> 00:22:34.154
-I got...
-Dad. I got it!

616
00:22:34.178 --> 00:22:35.223
Fine.

617
00:22:36.485 --> 00:22:38.158
Oh. my god. Dad.
you're not wearing any pants!

618
00:22:38.182 --> 00:22:39.638
And you're not wearing a bra!

619
00:22:39.662 --> 00:22:41.901
Oh. but we didn't think
that you would be up this early.

620
00:22:41.925 --> 00:22:45.862
You both have officially
<i>ruined</i> pumpkin spice for me.

621
00:22:45.886 --> 00:22:47.277
Don't forget your laundry.

622
00:22:59.029 --> 00:23:01.051
Hey. so. um...

623
00:23:01.075 --> 00:23:02.879
it occurred to me

624
00:23:02.903 --> 00:23:05.795
that we have a month
to finish our manuscript.

625
00:23:05.819 --> 00:23:07.100
so. I did the math.

626
00:23:07.124 --> 00:23:10.800
and if we each write
five pages a day.

627
00:23:10.824 --> 00:23:12.018
we should be fine.

628
00:23:12.042 --> 00:23:14.567
So. what do you think?

629
00:23:19.876 --> 00:23:21.680
You get freaky with my dad.

630
00:23:21.704 --> 00:23:23.160
and now
you're just gonna pretend

631
00:23:23.184 --> 00:23:24.596
like nothing ever happened?

632
00:23:24.620 --> 00:23:27.425
I was just taking your advice.
trying to have a little fun.

633
00:23:27.449 --> 00:23:30.385
You know. a "situations hip"
like you and...

634
00:23:30.409 --> 00:23:31.560
So that's what this is about?

635
00:23:31.584 --> 00:23:33.388
Right. right.

636
00:23:33.412 --> 00:23:35.607
So you're still mad at me
for hooking up with Oliver.

637
00:23:35.631 --> 00:23:37.870
so you hook up with my dad
to get back at me?

638
00:23:37.894 --> 00:23:39.089
That is not
what happened at all.

639
00:23:39.113 --> 00:23:40.960
That's exactly what happened!

640
00:23:40.984 --> 00:23:42.397
You used my dad
as a revenge hook-up.

641
00:23:42.421 --> 00:23:43.746
A w...?

642
00:23:43.770 --> 00:23:45.530
You know what?
You're a hypocrite.

643
00:23:45.554 --> 00:23:46.705
How am I a hypocrite?

644
00:23:46.729 --> 00:23:48.098
You can have a "boo thang!"

645
00:23:48.122 --> 00:23:49.752
But can I have a boo thang?

646
00:23:49.776 --> 00:23:52.189
No. no. no...
no boo thang <i>for me.</i>

647
00:23:52.213 --> 00:23:53.712
Stop saying "boo thang"!

648
00:23:53.736 --> 00:23:56.411
I am just calling it like it is.

649
00:23:56.435 --> 00:23:59.022
You know what I think?

650
00:23:59.046 --> 00:24:01.285
I think that you're scared

651
00:24:01.309 --> 00:24:02.939
of what you've got with Jack.

652
00:24:02.963 --> 00:24:03.983
Mm-hmm.

653
00:24:04.007 --> 00:24:05.942
You're scared of your feelings.

654
00:24:05.966 --> 00:24:07.813
you're scared
of falling for him.

655
00:24:07.837 --> 00:24:10.231
so you're sabotaging things
before they even start.

656
00:24:12.538 --> 00:24:14.190
{[door shuts in distance]

657
00:24:19.675 --> 00:24:21.174
Great.
Now look what you've done.

658
00:24:21.198 --> 00:24:23.350
Your dad is leaving.

659
00:24:23.374 --> 00:24:24.592
You chased him away.

660
00:24:30.599 --> 00:24:32.838
Hey! You're gonna leave
without saying goodbye?

661
00:24:32.862 --> 00:24:35.188
Whoa. take it down a notch.
kiddo. I'm not leaving.

662
00:24:35.212 --> 00:24:36.712
I just have to grab
something from in town.

663
00:24:36.736 --> 00:24:38.172
Oh.

664
00:24:40.043 --> 00:24:41.543
God.

665
00:24:41.567 --> 00:24:43.632
Ah. this frickin' thing.
These fobs never work.

666
00:24:43.656 --> 00:24:45.634
Whatever happened
to just using a key?

667
00:24:45.658 --> 00:24:46.765
I know. right?

668
00:24:46.789 --> 00:24:48.114
Wait!

669
00:24:48.138 --> 00:24:49.812
Don't call Triple-A.
Let me see the clicker thing...

670
00:24:49.836 --> 00:24:51.857
No. no. I'm not.
I'm just gonna use the app.

671
00:24:51.881 --> 00:24:54.033
These new trucks.
you can open them. start them.

672
00:24:54.057 --> 00:24:56.209
do whatever...
all from the app.

673
00:24:56.233 --> 00:24:58.124
There...

674
00:24:58.148 --> 00:24:59.279
Ah. see?

675
00:25:02.501 --> 00:25:04.783
That's it!
I know how it happened.

676
00:25:04.807 --> 00:25:06.263
What are you talking about?

677
00:25:06.287 --> 00:25:07.917
The garage door opener
had a Wi-Fi sticker on it.

678
00:25:07.941 --> 00:25:10.659
which means it could've
been opened with an app.

679
00:25:10.683 --> 00:25:12.399
Yes! Yes. yes!

680
00:25:12.423 --> 00:25:13.923
And Dean would've had the app
on his phone!

681
00:25:13.947 --> 00:25:15.402
What am I missing?

682
00:25:15.426 --> 00:25:17.187
We have an errand to run.
I'll be back in an hour.

683
00:25:17.211 --> 00:25:18.841
I love you...
but I'm still kinda mad at you.

684
00:25:18.865 --> 00:25:20.519
Let's go!

685
00:25:22.869 --> 00:25:25.108
Okay. is this some kind
of official investigation?

686
00:25:25.132 --> 00:25:26.457
Well. if it were
an official investigation.

687
00:25:26.481 --> 00:25:28.024
these two would not be here.
but you know what?

688
00:25:28.048 --> 00:25:29.504
We can make it official.
if you want.

689
00:25:29.528 --> 00:25:31.070
Hey. we don't have to do that.

690
00:25:31.094 --> 00:25:32.811
I've got nothing to hide.

691
00:25:32.835 --> 00:25:34.291
So I spoke
with the garage door company.

692
00:25:34.315 --> 00:25:35.422
Your garage door model

693
00:25:35.446 --> 00:25:37.294
is one
that can be opened with an app

694
00:25:37.318 --> 00:25:38.077
from anywhere.

695
00:25:38.101 --> 00:25:40.036
The garage door company

696
00:25:40.060 --> 00:25:41.690
requires a warrant
to share user records...

697
00:25:41.714 --> 00:25:42.778
which I'm working on...

698
00:25:42.802 --> 00:25:44.910
but what we have confirmed

699
00:25:44.934 --> 00:25:47.217
is that the phone that was used
to trigger your garage door

700
00:25:47.241 --> 00:25:49.262
on the day your wife died

701
00:25:49.286 --> 00:25:51.134
was using Wi-Fi
from the police station.

702
00:25:51.158 --> 00:25:54.074
which is exactly where you were
at the time of death.

703
00:25:55.249 --> 00:25:56.705
So you're saying
I opened that door.

704
00:25:56.729 --> 00:25:58.097
that I killed my wife?

705
00:25:58.121 --> 00:25:59.490
-What I'm saying is...
-Oh. cut the crap. Dean!

706
00:25:59.514 --> 00:26:01.361
You were having
multiple affairs.

707
00:26:01.385 --> 00:26:02.711
and you wanted
out of the marriage.

708
00:26:02.735 --> 00:26:03.886
but divorce would mean

709
00:26:03.910 --> 00:26:05.409
that you'd have
to split everything.

710
00:26:05.433 --> 00:26:07.280
including all the money

711
00:26:07.304 --> 00:26:08.934
from the sponsors.

712
00:26:08.958 --> 00:26:10.762
from when <i>Dean's Catch</i>
went viral.

713
00:26:10.786 --> 00:26:11.807
Look. it's not that much.
believe me.

714
00:26:11.831 --> 00:26:13.069
Wow!

715
00:26:13.093 --> 00:26:15.027
Well. the little fancy watch
on your wrist

716
00:26:15.051 --> 00:26:16.594
-says it is!
-I thought we agreed

717
00:26:16.618 --> 00:26:18.138
you weren't going to say
a single word.

718
00:26:19.055 --> 00:26:20.337
My lips are sealed.

719
00:26:20.361 --> 00:26:21.077
Are they?

720
00:26:21.101 --> 00:26:22.687
Yeah. Mm.

721
00:26:22.711 --> 00:26:23.993
Check the app.

722
00:26:24.017 --> 00:26:25.603
Hmm?

723
00:26:25.627 --> 00:26:29.128
I programmed my car
to open the garage door.

724
00:26:29.152 --> 00:26:30.565
He's telling the truth.

725
00:26:30.589 --> 00:26:31.696
This phone
did not open that door.

726
00:26:31.720 --> 00:26:32.720
Let me see.

727
00:26:34.070 --> 00:26:35.221
Okay.

728
00:26:35.245 --> 00:26:36.353
Okay. but look at this...

729
00:26:36.377 --> 00:26:37.876
it says that someone else
opened the garage door

730
00:26:37.900 --> 00:26:39.922
at the time
of Katherine's death.

731
00:26:39.946 --> 00:26:40.946
So who else had the app?

732
00:26:42.949 --> 00:26:44.037
Who else?

733
00:26:45.429 --> 00:26:46.581
It was Connie. all right?

734
00:26:46.605 --> 00:26:48.626
That's how she came and went.

735
00:26:48.650 --> 00:26:49.845
It was easier
than giving her keys.

736
00:26:49.869 --> 00:26:52.325
All right. that's crap!
He's playing us.

737
00:26:52.349 --> 00:26:53.349
Mm!

738
00:26:56.005 --> 00:26:58.157
Connie was
at the police station.

739
00:26:58.181 --> 00:27:00.270
and that's where
the signal came from.

740
00:27:05.885 --> 00:27:07.732
Live in three. Connie.

741
00:27:07.756 --> 00:27:10.822
We have clear skies
and a brisk. westerly wind

742
00:27:10.846 --> 00:27:12.563
for the Founders Cove
Fall Festival.

743
00:27:12.587 --> 00:27:15.914
where residents gather
to celebrate the harvest season

744
00:27:15.938 --> 00:27:18.264
with games. food.
and good times.

745
00:27:18.288 --> 00:27:19.657
I personally cannot wait

746
00:27:19.681 --> 00:27:21.485
for the good. old-fashioned
potluck tonight.

747
00:27:21.509 --> 00:27:23.966
That's all from me.
Connie Newsome.

748
00:27:23.990 --> 00:27:26.533
Back to you
in the studio. Brett.

749
00:27:26.557 --> 00:27:28.623
[camera operator
And... we're out.

750
00:27:28.647 --> 00:27:31.190
For God's sake.
let's get out of here.

751
00:27:31.214 --> 00:27:32.801
Pumpkin pie
makes me want to vomit.

752
00:27:32.825 --> 00:27:34.653
Oh. not yours.

753
00:27:36.785 --> 00:27:38.894
Connie Newsome.
I need to see your phone.

754
00:27:38.918 --> 00:27:40.330
Why?

755
00:27:40.354 --> 00:27:42.462
It may have been used
in the commission of a crime.

756
00:27:42.486 --> 00:27:44.247
-That's ridiculous.
-Well. a judge didn't think so.

757
00:27:44.271 --> 00:27:46.162
This is the warrant.

758
00:27:46.186 --> 00:27:47.709
Thank you.

759
00:27:49.232 --> 00:27:51.863
You have the app that controls
Dean Starkweather's garage.

760
00:27:51.887 --> 00:27:53.473
and your phone was used
to open that garage

761
00:27:53.497 --> 00:27:54.997
at the moment

762
00:27:55.021 --> 00:27:56.128
Katherine Stark weather
was killed.

763
00:27:56.152 --> 00:27:57.782
That can't be.

764
00:27:57.806 --> 00:28:00.437
Okay. Connie Newsome.
you're under arrest

765
00:28:00.461 --> 00:28:02.134
for the murder
of Katherine Stark weather.

766
00:28:02.158 --> 00:28:03.875
Are you serious?

767
00:28:03.899 --> 00:28:05.181
Let's go.

768
00:28:05.205 --> 00:28:07.270
You have the right
to remain silent.

769
00:28:07.294 --> 00:28:09.228
Anything you say can. and will.
be used against you...

770
00:28:09.252 --> 00:28:12.797
Your arch nemesis
arrested for murder.

771
00:28:12.821 --> 00:28:15.626
I guess you finally win.

772
00:28:15.650 --> 00:28:17.130
It doesn't feel like a win.

773
00:28:30.012 --> 00:28:32.121
Hey. We're gonna go for a walk.
You wanna come?

774
00:28:32.145 --> 00:28:35.211
Oh. um. I've got
a lot of paperwork to do.

775
00:28:35.235 --> 00:28:37.213
and you two need
Daddy-daughter time.

776
00:28:37.237 --> 00:28:39.065
-Okay.
-Okay.

777
00:28:48.291 --> 00:28:51.077
I swear. you are not
getting away with this.

778
00:28:54.645 --> 00:28:57.146
Watching me get arrested
wasn't enough for you?

779
00:28:57.170 --> 00:28:59.322
You needed to see
how I look in orange?

780
00:28:59.346 --> 00:29:00.932
Believe me. Connie...

781
00:29:00.956 --> 00:29:03.413
nothing would give me more joy
than watching you rot in jail.

782
00:29:03.437 --> 00:29:05.458
but I know
that you didn't kill Katherine.

783
00:29:05.482 --> 00:29:07.765
You fell for Dean.

784
00:29:07.789 --> 00:29:08.897
and you I both know
you've always had

785
00:29:08.921 --> 00:29:09.898
terrible taste in men.

786
00:29:09.922 --> 00:29:11.160
Almost as bad as yours.

787
00:29:11.184 --> 00:29:12.248
Do you want my help or not?

788
00:29:12.272 --> 00:29:13.510
Go ahead.

789
00:29:13.534 --> 00:29:14.598
As I was saying.

790
00:29:14.622 --> 00:29:16.078
you have terrible taste in men.

791
00:29:16.102 --> 00:29:18.167
you were desperate
to get rid of Katherine...

792
00:29:18.191 --> 00:29:19.516
You certainly know
what "desperate" feels like.

793
00:29:19.540 --> 00:29:21.107
Are we really gonna do this?

794
00:29:22.238 --> 00:29:23.215
Go on.

795
00:29:23.239 --> 00:29:25.000
All that said.

796
00:29:25.024 --> 00:29:27.002
I know damn well
you wouldn't murder her

797
00:29:27.026 --> 00:29:28.133
to get rid of her.

798
00:29:28.157 --> 00:29:29.526
How do you know for sure?

799
00:29:29.550 --> 00:29:31.267
Your lack of a violent history.

800
00:29:31.291 --> 00:29:33.748
your desperate need
for societal approval.

801
00:29:33.772 --> 00:29:35.097
and...

802
00:29:35.121 --> 00:29:37.577
the fact that this whole thing
was intricately planned.

803
00:29:37.601 --> 00:29:39.231
down to the very last detail.

804
00:29:39.255 --> 00:29:40.755
So you're saying

805
00:29:40.779 --> 00:29:43.018
that I'm not smart enough
to have murdered Katherine?

806
00:29:43.042 --> 00:29:44.193
Yup. more or less.

807
00:29:44.217 --> 00:29:45.716
The real question is

808
00:29:45.740 --> 00:29:47.849
whether Dean
was desperate enough

809
00:29:47.873 --> 00:29:49.657
to kill Katherine
to get out of the marriage.

810
00:29:51.485 --> 00:29:52.747
Honestly. I don't know.

811
00:29:53.922 --> 00:29:55.726
There was no love lost
between those two.

812
00:29:55.750 --> 00:29:58.207
and he promised me
he would leave her. but...

813
00:29:58.231 --> 00:29:59.599
But he was afraid.
if he divorced her.

814
00:29:59.623 --> 00:30:01.688
she would take all of his money.

815
00:30:01.712 --> 00:30:03.386
You don't even know
the half of it!

816
00:30:03.410 --> 00:30:04.822
He sold that podcast

817
00:30:04.846 --> 00:30:07.172
to a big media company
out of New York.

818
00:30:07.196 --> 00:30:08.521
We're talking mega-bucks.

819
00:30:08.545 --> 00:30:09.871
and the kicker is.

820
00:30:09.895 --> 00:30:12.221
I never asked for that damn
garage app on my phone.

821
00:30:12.245 --> 00:30:13.570
It was all his idea!

822
00:30:13.594 --> 00:30:15.093
When did he do that?

823
00:30:15.117 --> 00:30:16.423
About two weeks ago.

824
00:30:17.598 --> 00:30:19.228
So he didn't invite you
into that podcast

825
00:30:19.252 --> 00:30:21.621
to gang up on me and Andi.

826
00:30:21.645 --> 00:30:23.232
He wanted you close to him

827
00:30:23.256 --> 00:30:25.301
so he could get
into your phone and...

828
00:30:26.737 --> 00:30:29.610
use it to open the garage door.

829
00:30:30.785 --> 00:30:33.091
That son of a bitch!

830
00:30:45.408 --> 00:30:48.039
Oh. you can't be
leaving already?

831
00:30:48.063 --> 00:30:50.302
Yeah. the job in Portland...
I gotta get a move-on.

832
00:30:50.326 --> 00:30:52.391
Yeah.

833
00:30:52.415 --> 00:30:55.873
Oh. and the other. uh. project
has been taken care of.

834
00:30:55.897 --> 00:30:57.570
Oh. good. Thanks.

835
00:30:57.594 --> 00:30:58.876
What other project?

836
00:30:58.900 --> 00:31:01.357
-Um. just a bit of carpentry...
-Yeah.

837
00:31:01.381 --> 00:31:03.315
Work upstairs.

838
00:31:03.339 --> 00:31:04.534
What. did you two.

839
00:31:04.558 --> 00:31:05.864
like. break the bed
or something?

840
00:31:07.648 --> 00:31:09.171
-Uh...
-Oh. my God!

841
00:31:10.999 --> 00:31:12.542
I was joking!

842
00:31:12.566 --> 00:31:15.284
Because the thought
of two boomers

843
00:31:15.308 --> 00:31:16.851
breaking a bed having sex
is so ridiculous

844
00:31:16.875 --> 00:31:18.224
it couldn't possibly be true!

845
00:31:20.748 --> 00:31:22.334
So. thank you
for the hospitality.

846
00:31:22.358 --> 00:31:24.032
Oh...

847
00:31:24.056 --> 00:31:26.425
Um. any time.

848
00:31:26.449 --> 00:31:28.123
-Uh...
-Mm. yep. Yep.

849
00:31:28.147 --> 00:31:29.472
This is...

850
00:31:29.496 --> 00:31:30.995
Oh. for God's sakes!

851
00:31:31.019 --> 00:31:32.518
The damage is done.
You two can hug each other.

852
00:31:32.542 --> 00:31:34.849
Right.

853
00:31:36.590 --> 00:31:38.460
I hope to see you soon.

854
00:31:39.549 --> 00:31:41.421
Me too.

855
00:31:47.644 --> 00:31:49.361
-Don't flatter yourself.
-Hmm?

856
00:31:49.385 --> 00:31:50.928
She's just using you

857
00:31:50.952 --> 00:31:52.887
to get over
her own personal stuff.

858
00:31:52.911 --> 00:31:54.279
Ah. I'm fine with it.

859
00:31:54.303 --> 00:31:57.239
I got my own stuff
to work through.

860
00:31:57.263 --> 00:31:59.458
I'm sorry
if. uh. it makes you feel...

861
00:31:59.482 --> 00:32:00.851
Nauseated?

862
00:32:00.875 --> 00:32:02.897
No! Not at all.

863
00:32:02.921 --> 00:32:05.508
You know. it's been just
the two of us for so long.

864
00:32:05.532 --> 00:32:07.771
I forget
it's not my job to be your pal.

865
00:32:07.795 --> 00:32:09.536
It's my job to be your dad.

866
00:32:11.712 --> 00:32:13.366
You were a pretty good Mom. too.

867
00:32:15.455 --> 00:32:16.630
Thanks.

868
00:32:22.549 --> 00:32:23.942
I'm still looking for her.

869
00:32:25.987 --> 00:32:28.879
What are you expecting to find?

870
00:32:28.903 --> 00:32:30.794
I don't know.

871
00:32:30.818 --> 00:32:31.969
That's the point.

872
00:32:31.993 --> 00:32:33.623
Sweetheart. she's gone.

873
00:32:33.647 --> 00:32:34.929
You have to let her go.

874
00:32:34.953 --> 00:32:36.278
I have.

875
00:32:36.302 --> 00:32:38.019
But you two loved each other.

876
00:32:38.043 --> 00:32:40.108
Right. Yeah. look.

877
00:32:40.132 --> 00:32:42.675
I've never told you this. but...

878
00:32:42.699 --> 00:32:45.200
a year before
your mom disappeared.

879
00:32:45.224 --> 00:32:46.810
she had an affair.

880
00:32:46.834 --> 00:32:48.725
With who?

881
00:32:48.749 --> 00:32:50.205
Her boss...

882
00:32:50.229 --> 00:32:53.251
at the shipping company
that she worked at...

883
00:32:53.275 --> 00:32:55.060
Frank Getz.

884
00:32:56.452 --> 00:32:58.735
Everything just started
to fall apart after that.

885
00:32:58.759 --> 00:32:59.997
No.

886
00:33:00.021 --> 00:33:01.825
No. I don't believe it.

887
00:33:01.849 --> 00:33:04.436
No. I was young.
but I remember you two together.

888
00:33:04.460 --> 00:33:05.785
and you were so in love
with each other

889
00:33:05.809 --> 00:33:07.178
up until the very end.

890
00:33:07.202 --> 00:33:08.310
I thought so. too.

891
00:33:08.334 --> 00:33:10.312
But life is...

892
00:33:10.336 --> 00:33:12.749
complicated...

893
00:33:12.773 --> 00:33:15.273
and when you love someone
who doesn't love you back

894
00:33:15.297 --> 00:33:16.883
it's just...

895
00:33:16.907 --> 00:33:18.885
well. I had to let go.
sweetheart...

896
00:33:18.909 --> 00:33:19.954
to survive.

897
00:33:21.477 --> 00:33:24.152
I had a friend do a search...

898
00:33:24.176 --> 00:33:26.937
and he said that Mom's past
has been completely erased.

899
00:33:26.961 --> 00:33:29.070
All of her public records
are gone!

900
00:33:29.094 --> 00:33:30.941
She worked in I.T.

901
00:33:30.965 --> 00:33:32.987
I mean. she had the skills
to do it. if she wanted to.

902
00:33:33.011 --> 00:33:36.164
I think
she's hiding from someone.

903
00:33:36.188 --> 00:33:38.514
Sweetheart. I think
this might be hard to hear.

904
00:33:38.538 --> 00:33:40.472
but maybe it's...

905
00:33:40.496 --> 00:33:41.889
maybe she's hiding from us.

906
00:33:50.463 --> 00:33:53.616
<i>Dean. we have a message
from Carol in Watertown.</i>

907
00:33:53.640 --> 00:33:55.096
Look at this.

908
00:33:55.120 --> 00:33:57.402
It's right at the time
of Katherine's death.

909
00:33:57.426 --> 00:34:00.144
Ugh. I can't see if Connie's
holding her phone or not.

910
00:34:00.168 --> 00:34:02.146
I can't see
if Dean has a phone. either.

911
00:34:02.170 --> 00:34:03.563
but trust me. it is him.

912
00:34:04.825 --> 00:34:06.498
What made you go see Connie?

913
00:34:06.522 --> 00:34:08.979
Hmph. Connie and I have been
at each other for years.

914
00:34:09.003 --> 00:34:10.502
If she's a murderer.

915
00:34:10.526 --> 00:34:13.572
she would've killed me by now.

916
00:34:15.705 --> 00:34:19.033
Your dad left his shaving kit
in the guestroom bathroom.

917
00:34:19.057 --> 00:34:22.471
Hmm. you can deliver it to him.
maybe go for round two.

918
00:34:22.495 --> 00:34:24.821
I'm sorry that you think
I'm getting back at you

919
00:34:24.845 --> 00:34:27.650
for what happened with Oliver.
but that's not what's going on.

920
00:34:27.674 --> 00:34:29.217
It's Jack. isn't it?

921
00:34:29.241 --> 00:34:31.069
Maybe.

922
00:34:32.331 --> 00:34:34.048
What's the problem?

923
00:34:34.072 --> 00:34:35.745
I mean. you think
he's gonna go squirrelly on you

924
00:34:35.769 --> 00:34:37.355
and steal your snowblower?

925
00:34:37.379 --> 00:34:38.617
Wouldn't be the first time.

926
00:34:38.641 --> 00:34:40.033
True.

927
00:34:41.470 --> 00:34:43.405
Okay. we're not
getting anywhere with this.

928
00:34:43.429 --> 00:34:45.668
I need a new angle to see
if Connie has her phone or not.

929
00:34:45.692 --> 00:34:48.323
The only cameras there
were the ones for the pod-show.

930
00:34:48.347 --> 00:34:49.435
"Podcast."

931
00:34:50.566 --> 00:34:52.022
There was probably
another camera.

932
00:34:52.046 --> 00:34:53.154
but it doesn't work.

933
00:34:53.178 --> 00:34:54.329
What other camera?

934
00:34:54.353 --> 00:34:56.244
All police stations
have surveillance cameras.

935
00:34:56.268 --> 00:34:58.159
but you said there's
an ordinance in Founders Cove

936
00:34:58.183 --> 00:34:59.986
that doesn't allow them
to actually record.

937
00:35:00.010 --> 00:35:01.292
Yeah. but that's
a city ordinance.

938
00:35:01.316 --> 00:35:03.274
The Sheriff's Office is County.

939
00:35:06.016 --> 00:35:07.104
Hmm!

940
00:35:10.673 --> 00:35:11.781
Here it is.

941
00:35:11.805 --> 00:35:14.653
Okay. okay.
There's Dean's phone.

942
00:35:14.677 --> 00:35:16.220
Connie was sitting
right next to him.

943
00:35:16.244 --> 00:35:17.569
just like he planned it.

944
00:35:17.593 --> 00:35:19.267
I remember
she put her phone down.

945
00:35:19.291 --> 00:35:20.616
If he picked it up.
we'll see it.

946
00:35:20.640 --> 00:35:23.445
Fast-forward a little.

947
00:35:23.469 --> 00:35:25.253
Okay... here she is.

948
00:35:27.864 --> 00:35:29.625
There he is. Mr. Big-Shot.

949
00:35:29.649 --> 00:35:31.540
laughing and talking.

950
00:35:31.564 --> 00:35:34.087
Well. yuck it up. bozo!
You're about to go down hard.

951
00:35:36.046 --> 00:35:37.459
Okay. here it comes.

952
00:35:37.483 --> 00:35:39.591
Just watch... he's gonna
reach over for that phone...

953
00:35:39.615 --> 00:35:40.723
Shit!

954
00:35:40.747 --> 00:35:41.985
That light's
blocking everything.

955
00:35:42.009 --> 00:35:43.378
Is there another angle?

956
00:35:43.402 --> 00:35:44.596
That's the only camera
in the bullpen.

957
00:35:44.620 --> 00:35:46.598
'Course it is.

958
00:35:46.622 --> 00:35:48.383
Unless someone else...

959
00:35:48.407 --> 00:35:51.168
in the room was recording.

960
00:35:51.192 --> 00:35:52.517
<i>Sorry I'm late.</i>

961
00:35:52.541 --> 00:35:54.824
Of course I have footage!

962
00:35:54.848 --> 00:35:57.155
I recorded the entire interview.

963
00:35:58.373 --> 00:35:59.655
-Here we go...
-Yeah.

964
00:35:59.679 --> 00:36:01.483
A clear view!

965
00:36:01.507 --> 00:36:03.267
Oh. I could kiss you. Norman!

966
00:36:03.291 --> 00:36:04.877
I told you I was essential.

967
00:36:04.901 --> 00:36:07.033
Fast-forward to the time
of Katherine's death. please?

968
00:36:09.254 --> 00:36:10.579
Okay. right there!

969
00:36:10.603 --> 00:36:12.711
Look. there's Dean.
and there's Connie.

970
00:36:12.735 --> 00:36:15.714
Watch what he does
in three. two. one...

971
00:36:15.738 --> 00:36:16.999
<i>for murder. am I right?</i>

972
00:36:18.306 --> 00:36:19.805
Well. I'll be...

973
00:36:19.829 --> 00:36:21.894
Oh. my God.
It was Juliette?

974
00:36:21.918 --> 00:36:23.418
Pause that.

975
00:36:23.442 --> 00:36:24.549
No. it-it can't be.

976
00:36:24.573 --> 00:36:25.811
But it is.

977
00:36:25.835 --> 00:36:27.161
It's Juliette. not Dean.

978
00:36:27.185 --> 00:36:28.553
I never would have guessed.

979
00:36:28.577 --> 00:36:29.511
Me neither.

980
00:36:29.535 --> 00:36:31.904
Well. that's it. Norman.

981
00:36:31.928 --> 00:36:33.732
You solved the case!

982
00:36:33.756 --> 00:36:36.170
He didn't actually <i>solve</i> it.

983
00:36:36.194 --> 00:36:37.258
I'm having dinner
with the President

984
00:36:37.282 --> 00:36:39.042
of the West Coast Chapter
of the Cloudies.

985
00:36:39.066 --> 00:36:40.957
Those Westies always think
they're better than us.

986
00:36:40.981 --> 00:36:42.088
Wait till I tell!

987
00:36:42.112 --> 00:36:44.723
Noah. keep an eye on him.

988
00:36:45.986 --> 00:36:49.008
This can't be happening.

989
00:36:49.032 --> 00:36:52.098
Okay. but it kind of
makes sense. though.

990
00:36:52.122 --> 00:36:55.101
Right? I mean.
Juliette was super-into Dean.

991
00:36:55.125 --> 00:36:57.191
and she hated that he was
fooling around with Connie.

992
00:36:57.215 --> 00:36:58.496
and she's probably the one

993
00:36:58.520 --> 00:36:59.845
who put the app
on Connie's phone.

994
00:36:59.869 --> 00:37:01.107
so she had the password.

995
00:37:01.131 --> 00:37:02.674
All she had to do
was hit the icon

996
00:37:02.698 --> 00:37:04.589
to make the garage go.

997
00:37:04.613 --> 00:37:06.417
So how'd she stage the suicide?

998
00:37:06.441 --> 00:37:07.940
She knew Katherine.

999
00:37:07.964 --> 00:37:09.377
They were friends.

1000
00:37:09.401 --> 00:37:10.856
She probably went over
to the house

1001
00:37:10.880 --> 00:37:12.945
after Dean had left for work.

1002
00:37:12.969 --> 00:37:14.643
and slipped the pills
in her coffee

1003
00:37:14.667 --> 00:37:17.733
and then set the whole scene
in the garage.

1004
00:37:17.757 --> 00:37:18.864
So you...

1005
00:37:18.888 --> 00:37:20.692
you're saying that I was...

1006
00:37:20.716 --> 00:37:22.041
wrong?

1007
00:37:22.065 --> 00:37:23.283
That's right.

1008
00:37:24.242 --> 00:37:26.220
Wh... you were the one

1009
00:37:26.244 --> 00:37:28.352
who knew that it was a murder
and not a suicide.

1010
00:37:28.376 --> 00:37:29.571
and you knew

1011
00:37:29.595 --> 00:37:31.355
that it was Juliette
in Dean's hotel room.

1012
00:37:31.379 --> 00:37:33.488
and it was the perfect alibi...
you were right about that!

1013
00:37:33.512 --> 00:37:35.838
Going live on air
in front of a million people?

1014
00:37:35.862 --> 00:37:39.276
But I-I thought
that Dean was the killer.

1015
00:37:39.300 --> 00:37:41.868
You were only off by one person.

1016
00:37:43.870 --> 00:37:44.890
-Yeah.
-See you later.

1017
00:37:44.914 --> 00:37:46.370
Bye-bye.

1018
00:37:46.394 --> 00:37:48.067
Whoa! If it isn't
Founders Cove's finest.

1019
00:37:48.091 --> 00:37:49.982
and their
crime-fighting friends!

1020
00:37:50.006 --> 00:37:51.201
Hey. Jules. let's go live.

1021
00:37:51.225 --> 00:37:53.247
Juliette Daestrom.
you're under arrest

1022
00:37:53.271 --> 00:37:54.378
for the murder
of Katherine Stark weather.

1023
00:37:54.402 --> 00:37:55.988
You have the right
to remain silent.

1024
00:37:56.012 --> 00:37:58.034
Turn around.

1025
00:37:58.058 --> 00:37:59.209
Wait. Wait-wait-wait.

1026
00:37:59.233 --> 00:38:00.384
Hold up here.

1027
00:38:00.408 --> 00:38:01.994
Are you telling me
Juliette killed my wife?

1028
00:38:02.018 --> 00:38:03.126
Yeah. she sure did!

1029
00:38:03.150 --> 00:38:04.954
And she framed Connie
for it. too.

1030
00:38:04.978 --> 00:38:06.434
She thought that.

1031
00:38:06.458 --> 00:38:08.479
with Katherine gone
and Connie in prison.

1032
00:38:08.503 --> 00:38:10.264
she'd eliminated
the competition.

1033
00:38:10.288 --> 00:38:12.614
and could have you
all to herself.

1034
00:38:12.638 --> 00:38:14.292
Is this true?

1035
00:38:16.424 --> 00:38:18.359
I'm not saying anything
without my lawyer.

1036
00:38:18.383 --> 00:38:19.948
Yep.

1037
00:38:21.299 --> 00:38:22.624
Juliette Daestrom.

1038
00:38:22.648 --> 00:38:24.060
you have the right
to remain silent.

1039
00:38:24.084 --> 00:38:26.204
Anything you say can. and will.
be used against you...

1040
00:38:27.261 --> 00:38:28.341
I don't know how you do it.

1041
00:38:29.437 --> 00:38:31.633
I didn't do anything.

1042
00:38:31.657 --> 00:38:32.764
I thought it was you.

1043
00:38:32.788 --> 00:38:35.637
Me? You're kidding.

1044
00:38:35.661 --> 00:38:37.726
You may not be guilty.
but you still suck.

1045
00:38:37.750 --> 00:38:40.250
Hey. as long as
it pulls in an audience.

1046
00:38:40.274 --> 00:38:41.319
I'm okay with that.

1047
00:38:43.277 --> 00:38:45.429
I don't know if
you've been on socials lately...

1048
00:38:45.453 --> 00:38:46.387
forget I asked...

1049
00:38:46.411 --> 00:38:47.649
but...

1050
00:38:47.673 --> 00:38:49.259
Norman's video
of the police station?

1051
00:38:49.283 --> 00:38:50.695
It's been breaking the internet.

1052
00:38:50.719 --> 00:38:54.786
Oh. yeah-yeah-yeah.
You can't have too much video.

1053
00:38:54.810 --> 00:38:56.484
Nope.

1054
00:38:56.508 --> 00:38:59.400
Well. I'm glad we didn't
forget about Norman.

1055
00:38:59.424 --> 00:39:00.662
-Yeah.
-Wait a minute.

1056
00:39:00.686 --> 00:39:03.229
The-The surveillance video...

1057
00:39:03.253 --> 00:39:04.492
we forgot about it!

1058
00:39:04.516 --> 00:39:06.145
What are you talking about?
Are you having a stroke?

1059
00:39:06.169 --> 00:39:08.452
We already watched
the police surveillance video.

1060
00:39:08.476 --> 00:39:10.846
No. not in the police station...
the donut shop in Montpelier.

1061
00:39:10.870 --> 00:39:12.543
where they found
your mom's fingerprints.

1062
00:39:12.567 --> 00:39:14.153
There's gotta be
security footage!

1063
00:39:14.177 --> 00:39:16.504
Allie. that was three years ago.
It's probably gone by now.

1064
00:39:16.528 --> 00:39:18.332
But there was a robbery.
so maybe...

1065
00:39:18.356 --> 00:39:19.811
Maybe.

1066
00:39:19.835 --> 00:39:21.335
I'll ask Jack.

1067
00:39:21.359 --> 00:39:23.641
Great. Okay.
I need to lie down. It's...

1068
00:39:23.665 --> 00:39:24.947
Okay.

1069
00:39:24.971 --> 00:39:26.494
It's been a long day.

1070
00:39:35.634 --> 00:39:38.637
I want to thank you
for your help today.

1071
00:39:39.855 --> 00:39:41.703
Did Andi ask you about...

1072
00:39:41.727 --> 00:39:43.052
The donut shop? Yeah.

1073
00:39:43.076 --> 00:39:44.836
Let me see what I can do.

1074
00:39:44.860 --> 00:39:45.992
Mm. good.

1075
00:39:47.210 --> 00:39:49.256
But. for the record...

1076
00:39:52.172 --> 00:39:54.672
I was not at all helpful.

1077
00:39:54.696 --> 00:39:56.761
I got this one totally wrong.

1078
00:39:56.785 --> 00:39:58.241
No.

1079
00:39:58.265 --> 00:39:59.721
No one bats a thousand.

1080
00:39:59.745 --> 00:40:02.854
and this was a tough one
to crack...

1081
00:40:02.878 --> 00:40:04.706
just like you.

1082
00:40:06.273 --> 00:40:08.317
I'm not "tough to crack".

1083
00:40:10.233 --> 00:40:11.602
Allie. whatever's
going on with you.

1084
00:40:11.626 --> 00:40:14.933
it's just none of my business.
and I'll just stay out of it.

1085
00:40:16.675 --> 00:40:18.174
Thank you.

1086
00:40:18.198 --> 00:40:20.002
But. for what it's worth...

1087
00:40:20.026 --> 00:40:21.960
the invitation still stands.

1088
00:40:21.984 --> 00:40:23.614
If you ever want
to catch a movie with me.

1089
00:40:23.638 --> 00:40:25.703
I'll bring the popcorn.

1090
00:40:25.727 --> 00:40:26.704
Jack?

1091
00:40:26.728 --> 00:40:27.966
Yeah?

1092
00:40:27.990 --> 00:40:30.360
I do this thing...

1093
00:40:30.384 --> 00:40:31.927
where I-I...

1094
00:40:31.951 --> 00:40:32.710
rush into things.

1095
00:40:32.734 --> 00:40:34.756
and. uh. it's-it's not good.

1096
00:40:34.780 --> 00:40:38.107
so it just might take me
some time to. um...

1097
00:40:38.131 --> 00:40:40.457
figure it all out.

1098
00:40:40.481 --> 00:40:41.806
Well...

1099
00:40:41.830 --> 00:40:44.179
I'm a patient man.

1100
00:40:50.360 --> 00:40:51.816
Huh.

1101
00:40:51.840 --> 00:40:53.427
Hope that was as awkward
as it looked!

1102
00:40:53.451 --> 00:40:54.863
I'm an idiot.

1103
00:40:54.887 --> 00:40:56.255
Why?

1104
00:40:56.279 --> 00:40:58.997
For overthinking everything...

1105
00:40:59.021 --> 00:41:01.043
for being afraid
of my feelings for Jack.

1106
00:41:01.067 --> 00:41:02.392
for sleeping with your dad.

1107
00:41:02.416 --> 00:41:03.915
Ohh!

1108
00:41:03.939 --> 00:41:06.527
I'm supposed to be
the queen of romance.

1109
00:41:06.551 --> 00:41:07.943
Why can't I get this right?

1110
00:41:11.164 --> 00:41:12.905
I know exactly what you need.

1111
00:41:17.300 --> 00:41:18.649
Mm...

1112
00:41:19.738 --> 00:41:21.585
this is so effing good!

1113
00:41:21.609 --> 00:41:24.632
There is nothing that
a slice of pie can't fix.

1114
00:41:24.656 --> 00:41:26.547
<i>Mainly sunny
the rest of the week.</i>

1115
00:41:26.571 --> 00:41:28.723
<i>but watch out
for that wind on Saturday.</i>

1116
00:41:28.747 --> 00:41:31.116
<i>On a personal note.
I have some big news...</i>

1117
00:41:31.140 --> 00:41:32.553
<i>my recent brush with the law</i>

1118
00:41:32.577 --> 00:41:34.685
<i>has inspired me
to put pen to paper</i>

1119
00:41:34.709 --> 00:41:37.427
<i>and write
my own mystery novel...</i>

1120
00:41:37.451 --> 00:41:39.473
<i>"The Forecast is Murder."</i>

1121
00:41:39.497 --> 00:41:40.952
-Oh. for God's...
-Are you kidding me?

1122
00:41:40.976 --> 00:41:42.214
<i>Of a weather reporter who...</i>

1123
00:41:42.238 --> 00:41:44.438
-Can you please turn that off?
-Can you turn that off?

1124
00:41:45.764 --> 00:41:48.069
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

1125
00:41:49.942 --> 00:41:51.267
All right. well...

1126
00:41:51.291 --> 00:41:53.356
I figured out
why I'm so off my game.

1127
00:41:53.380 --> 00:41:54.923
You're not off your game.

1128
00:41:54.947 --> 00:41:55.924
Mm-mm. I am.

1129
00:41:55.948 --> 00:41:58.056
It's the whole <i>boo thang</i> thing.

1130
00:41:58.080 --> 00:42:00.058
Like. it's fine for you...
I know it is...

1131
00:42:00.082 --> 00:42:01.320
but I can't do it.

1132
00:42:01.344 --> 00:42:03.497
It's completely
crashed my brain.

1133
00:42:03.521 --> 00:42:05.020
It's your kryptonite.

1134
00:42:05.044 --> 00:42:06.238
That's exactly what it is!

1135
00:42:06.262 --> 00:42:07.544
Remember. when I was mad at you

1136
00:42:07.568 --> 00:42:09.111
when you said
that I was with your dad

1137
00:42:09.135 --> 00:42:11.113
because I was afraid
of my feelings for Jack?

1138
00:42:11.137 --> 00:42:12.506
You were right.

1139
00:42:12.530 --> 00:42:14.246
but here's the problem...

1140
00:42:14.270 --> 00:42:17.859
I get so swept off my feet
by the romance of everything

1141
00:42:17.883 --> 00:42:19.382
that I run off
and I marry the guy.

1142
00:42:19.406 --> 00:42:21.689
and then I realize later
that I made a huge mistake.

1143
00:42:21.713 --> 00:42:23.429
and I divorce him...
it's a vicious cycle.

1144
00:42:23.453 --> 00:42:25.301
At least you're self-aware.

1145
00:42:25.325 --> 00:42:28.522
Oh. definitely self-aware.
but enough about me.

1146
00:42:28.546 --> 00:42:30.785
I really don't think
you should be mad at your dad.

1147
00:42:30.809 --> 00:42:34.136
Mm... did I ask
for your opinion on that?

1148
00:42:34.160 --> 00:42:36.225
No. you didn't.
but you're getting it anyway.

1149
00:42:36.249 --> 00:42:37.685
I know.

1150
00:42:44.126 --> 00:42:46.825
♪ I think this is the start

1151
00:42:49.088 --> 00:42:52.720
♪ I think this is the part

1152
00:42:52.744 --> 00:42:55.007
♪ When it gets good

1153
00:42:57.923 --> 00:43:00.447
♪ When it gets good

1154
00:43:01.579 --> 00:43:03.557
♪ This is the part

1155
00:43:03.581 --> 00:43:05.017
♪ When it gets good
